section.section:
In consultation with the Secretary, the Insurance Commissioner may adjust the initial surplus requirement for a managed care organization that is not licensed as a health maintenance organization. In determining whether to make an adjustment under this paragraph, the Commissioner shall consider:
The proposed capitation level that would be received by the managed care organization under a contract with the Department under this subtitle;
The proposed range of benefits to be provided under a contract with the Department under this subtitle;
The existence of any commitment by the Secretary to designate funds over and above the proposed capitation where the designated funds:
The availability of the money held in trust by the Secretary to pay claims in case of impairment or insolvency of the managed care organization.
